<h1>Code Challenge: Fix This Form</h1>
<section>
    <form action="https://us-central1-nucamp-production.cloudfunctions.net/post/formdata" method="post">
        <div>
            <label for="travel">Preferred method of travel:</label>
            <select id="travel" required>
                <option disabled selected value="">Choose ... </option>
                <option value="bike">Bike</option>
                <option value="car">Car</option>
                <option value="train">Train</option>
            </select>
        </div>
        <div>
            Travel Budget:
            <input type="radio" id="frugal" name="budget" value="frugal" required/>
            <label>Frugal</label>
            <input type="radio" id="moderate" name="budget" value="moderate" required/>
            <label>Moderate</label>
            <input type="radio" id="luxury" name="budget" value="luxury" required/>
            <label>Luxury</label>
        </div>
        <div>
            <input type="submit" value="Go!" />
        </div>
    </form>
</section>

<!-- You do not need to change any code in the section below, it's just the instructions text -->

<hr />
<section>
    <h2>Instructions</h2>
    <p>There are a few mistakes in the form you see above. Log into Codepen if you haven't, then fork this Code Challenge (find the Fork button on the bottom right) to your own account. Find and fix these errors:</p>
    <ol>
        <li>If you select a method of travel from the dropdown list and submit the form, the value does not show up in the echo back from the server. How can you fix it so that whatever value you choose from the dropdown shows up when you submit the form?</li>
        <li>If you click on the labels "Frugal", "Moderate", or "Luxury" it does not focus on the associated radio button. How can you fix it so that clicking on each label will focus the correct radio button?</li>
        <li>You should only be able to select one option from the three radio buttons. Right now, you can click on both the radio buttons for "Moderate" and "Luxury" and they will both be selected. How can you fix it so that only one can be selected at a time from all three?</li>
    </ol>
</section>

